# File Naming

Use **camelCase** for all source file names in this project. Do not use PascalCase for file names.

## Rules

- **TypeScript/JavaScript**: `camelCase.ts`, `camelCase.tsx`, `camelCase.js`
- **One main export per file**: Name the file after its primary export (e.g. `rconManager.ts` exports `RconManager`, `dysStatsHandler.ts` exports handler logic).
- **Class/component names** stay PascalCase in code; only the **filename** is camelCase.

## Examples

- ✅ `rconManager.ts`, `rconClient.ts`, `logParser.ts`, `logWatcher.ts`
- ✅ `dysStatsHandler.ts`, `appWindow.ts`, `playerReputationHandler.ts`, `rconAppBackendData.ts`
- ❌ `RconManager.ts`, `LogParser.ts`, `AppWindow.ts`

## Rationale

Consistent camelCase filenames match the rest of the codebase and avoid mixing conventions (PascalCase for files vs. camelCase elsewhere).
